    source: JOURNAL-000
    observable: Bootstrap initialized a project with separate graphify-out, scribe-out, and SCRIBE memory surfaces.
  liens_causaux:
    source: JOURNAL-000
- id: PAT-GIT-001
  date: '2026-05-26'
  schema_patch_date: '2026-05-26'
  tier: hot
  status: ACTIVE
  titre: Agent artifact versioning boundary
  l0_abstract: Commit/push product source by default; share AGENT-MEMOIRE_PROJECT_STATUS.scribe only when causal memory should
    be collaborative, never graphify-out or scribe-out by default.
  scope: git-artifacts
  evidence:
    type: REASONED
    source: JOURNAL-000
    observable: graphify-out and scribe-out are generated local state, while AGENT-MEMOIRE_PROJECT_STATUS.scribe is optional
      shared causal memory.
  liens_causaux:
    source: JOURNAL-000
  confirmed_sessions:
  - session: JOURNAL-000
    observable: Bootstrap documented generated artifact boundary.
  - session: JOURNAL-MIGRATION-20260526
    observable: Migration kept scribe-out generated state ignored and committed only canonical memory.
- id: PAT-EOM-VOLUME-PROFILE-COMPOSITE-CONTRACT-001
  date: '2026-05-26'
  schema_patch_date: '2026-05-26'
  tier: hot
  status: ACTIVE
  titre: EOM independent, Volume Profile composite with data-quality honesty
  l0_abstract: Keep EOM as a separate zero-line oscillator, while Volume Profile toggles rows plus POC/VAH/VAL together and
    must disclose daily OHLCV approximation when intraday/trades are unavailable.
  scope: legacy-import/pat-eom-volume-profile-composite-contract-001
  evidence:
    type: OBSERVED
    source: JOURNAL-001
    observable: The requested feature required mixing a separate pane oscillator with a price-overlay composite profile without
      letting either alter unrelated chart scales.
  liens_causaux:
    source: JOURNAL-001
- id: PAT-PIVOT-POINTS-FAMILY-COMPOSITE-CONTRACT-001
  date: '2026-05-26'
  schema_patch_date: '2026-05-26'
  tier: hot
  status: ACTIVE
  titre: Pivot families are complete horizontal-level composites
  l0_abstract: Model Standard and Fibonacci Pivot Points as separate parent composites; each parent owns its central pivot
    plus all R/S levels so the UI never reuses a Standard card inside the Fibonacci family.
  scope: legacy-import/pat-pivot-points-family-composite-contract-001
  evidence:
    type: OBSERVED
    source: JOURNAL-002
    observable: The pivot UI ambiguity came from overlapping output keys and incomplete Fibonacci children, which made the
      catalog show the wrong parent/card relationship.
  liens_causaux:
    source: JOURNAL-002
- id: PAT-DIRECTIONAL-AROON-COMPOSITE-BOUNDARY-001
  description: Les familles directionnelles doivent distinguer parents composites, enfants graphiques et derives atomiques.
  application: ADX/DMI active ADX/+DI/-DI avec Trend Strength comme interpretation; Aroon active Up/Down; Aroon Osc calcule
    Up - Down en interne mais affiche une seule ligne autonome.
  virus: Traiter Aroon Osc comme un enfant visuel obligatoire d'Aroon, ou dessiner Trend Strength comme une courbe, cree une
    lecture technique fausse.
  antidote: Un calcul interne ne devient pas une sortie graphique; seules les sorties explicitement visibles dans le contrat
    UI doivent etre rendues.
  status: ACTIVE
  tier: warm
  titre: PAT-DIRECTIONAL-AROON-COMPOSITE-BOUNDARY-001
  l0_abstract: Les familles directionnelles doivent distinguer parents composites, enfants graphiques et derives atomiques.
  schema_patch_date: '2026-05-26'
